You are debugging a production issue where a high-throughput Java 21 Spring Boot application utilizing Virtual Threads experiences severe performance degradation. Thread dumps reveal that carrier threads are constantly blocked, preventing other virtual threads from executing. You locate the following snippet in a legacy class:

java
public class DataIngestionService {
    private final Object lock = new Object();

    public void ingestData(Payload data) {
        synchronized (lock) {
            // Blocking network call to external API
            restTemplate.postForEntity(\"https://api.example.com/data\", data, String.class);
        }
    }
}

